subSubSection.paragraph:
Male palp (
Figs 235‒237
): Tibial apophysis slender, as long as its diameter, constricted in the middle, with broadly truncate tip; embolar apophysis much shorter than embolus, with only slightly bent margins, getting somewhat broader distally, terminally bluntly pointed.

Epigyne (
Figs 238‒240
): Elongated, 1.4 x longer than wide, with rounded hood, which is much narrower than the total epigyne; pro-fovea somewhat longer than fovea; lateral pockets sac-like.
